UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. MISSOURI PACIFIC RAILROAD COMPANY, Appellee. No. 16777. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. May 22, 1958.

Before HUTCHESON, Chief Judge, and RIVES and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that Appellee’s Second Petition for Rehearing in the above entitled and numbered cause be, and it is hereby, denied.
